    • Constructor Detail

      • Iff

        public Iff(Predicate<? super P> predicate,
           Function<? super P,? extends R> f1,
           Function<? super P,? extends R> f2)
        Deprecated. 
        With this class one is able to compose a higher order function containing an if-clause. Constructs a new object of type Function providing the functionality of an if-clause. If the given predicate returns true for the first argument the function f1 will be invoked with this argument, otherwise the function f2 will be invoked. The function value will be returned.
        Parameters:
        predicate - predicate providing the functionality of an if-clause. If the predicate returns true, the if-branch will be executed resp. the first given function invoked, otherwise (false was been returned) the else-branch will be executed.
        f1 - function invoked in the if-branch.
        f2 - function invoked in the else-branch.

    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        public R invoke(List<? extends P> arguments)
        Deprecated. 
        Returns the result of the function as an object controlled by the given predicate. If the predicate returns true for the given arguments the function of the if-branch will be invoked otherwise the function of the else-branch will be invoked.
        Specified by:

        Overrides:

        Parameters:
        arguments - function arguments.
        Returns:
        the result of the function.
